The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically with properties of edge-colored vertex-ordered graphs and matrices over a finite alphabet. The paper also discusses a removal lemma and a Ramsey-type lemma, which are common topics in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
